race.description: Jt Project Group Super Maiden Plate
race.comment: ATTRACTIVENESS (8) no match for the classy Caffe Florian on debut when a respectable fourth over 1100m at Canterbury. Will appreciate the drop in grade and extra distance from the low gate. Go close. APERITAS (7) three-year-old filly by Exceed And Excel from Thermosphere on debut for the Michael Freedman yard. Has looked sharp in her two latest trials and gets her chance from the barrier. TAHURANGI (12) best performance in four starts when she launched late for a narrow second over 1200m at this track. Has a fitness edge over the bulk of these from the right gate. Each-way player. MARK OF GLORY (11) I Am Invincible filly from Mark Two on debut for the O'Shea & Charlton yard. Shown ability in the two trials and the lugging-bit and tongue-tie go on.
